PX, you went to a PX in Nam? <br>
They had a PX in Nam?<br>
The only exchange I knew of was when we traded the spoils of war with rear-echalon Commanding officers, so that could go home and show their cousins what they had captured.<br><br>
Used to pay mama-son $20.00 for strands of hair which we knitted into braids and sold to Naval and Air Force personnel in Da Nang as scalps we had taken from the enemy. Usually got two-three cases of beer, 2-3 cases of cokes and a few other items thrown in. Is that the PX your talking about.<br><br>
I do remember the car wash though, During some Da Nang runs, I would pull into it, with the Captain in the open jeep. He just couldn’t understand why he always got wet and the water never fell on me. I guess it was the insect repellant we used as cologne, when we went into town. Had to smell pretty, otherwise no one would trade with us.<br><br>
No need to frag new 2nd looies. In the jungle we just peeled off one by one until the Lt. figured out no one was following him and he was out there all alone. Usually didn't have any trouble with them after that.<br><br>

